        <abstract>
            <p>Discusses extinction of ammonites.</p>
            <p>Discusses August Krohn’s cirripede research and Krohn’s correction of his own work.</p>
            <p>Discusses origin of dog in connection with origin of man.</p>
            <p>Comments on the guinea-pig in South America.</p>
            <p>Notes K. E. von Baer’s view of species.</p>
            <p>Mentions difficulty of crossing rabbit and hare.</p>
            <p>Agrees with Hooker’s views on variation under cultivation and in nature.</p>
            <p>Regrets use of term "natural selection", would now use "Natural Preservation".</p>
        </abstract>
